08/11/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Retired Republika Srpska (RS) Army General Novak Djukic, suspected of war crimes against civilians, was arrested early Wednesday (November 7th) near Banja Luka.
Djukic, 52, is alleged to have been involved in the May 25th 1995, events in the northern town of Tuzla, where a single artillery round fired by the RS Army killed 71 people and injured dozens more.
It was considered one of the single worst incidents of the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict.
(Studio B, Fena, NTV Hayat, Nezavisne Novine, RTRS, SRNA, B92, Beta, AP, Reuters, BIRN, DPA - 07/11/07)
